## 2. Conceptual ER Diagram — Tables & Relationships

```mermaid
erDiagram
    USER ||--o{ APPOINTMENT : "books"
    USER ||--o{ STAFF_SERVICE_TYPE : "assigned_to"
    USER ||--o{ AUDIT_LOG : "performed_by"
    BRANCH ||--o{ SLOT : "has"
    BRANCH ||--o{ USER : "belongs_to (staff)"
    SERVICE_TYPE ||--o{ SLOT : "offered_in"
    SERVICE_TYPE ||--o{ STAFF_SERVICE_TYPE : "links"
    SLOT ||--o{ APPOINTMENT : "reserved_via"

    USER {
        uuid id PK
        string full_name
        string email UK
        string phone
        string password_hash
        enum role "admin | branch_manager | staff | customer"
        uuid branch_id FK "nullable for admin/customer"
        boolean is_active
        timestamp created_at
        timestamp updated_at
    }

    BRANCH {
        uuid id PK
        string name UK
        string address
        string city
        string phone
        boolean is_active
        timestamp created_at
        timestamp updated_at
    }

    SERVICE_TYPE {
        uuid id PK
        string name UK
        text description
        int duration_minutes
        boolean is_active
        timestamp created_at
    }

    STAFF_SERVICE_TYPE {
        uuid id PK
        uuid staff_id FK
        uuid service_type_id FK
        "UNIQUE(staff_id, service_type_id)"
    }

    SLOT {
        uuid id PK
        uuid branch_id FK
        uuid service_type_id FK
        date slot_date
        time start_time
        time end_time
        int max_bookings
        int current_bookings
        boolean is_active
        timestamp deleted_at "soft delete"
        timestamp created_at
        timestamp updated_at
    }

    APPOINTMENT {
        uuid id PK
        uuid customer_id FK
        uuid slot_id FK
        uuid staff_id FK "nullable"
        enum status "booked | cancelled | completed | no_show | rescheduled"
        string cancellation_reason
        string attachment_url
        string id_document_url
        timestamp booked_at
        timestamp cancelled_at
        timestamp rescheduled_from "ref to previous appointment"
        timestamp created_at
        timestamp updated_at
    }

    AUDIT_LOG {
        uuid id PK
        uuid user_id FK
        string action
        string entity_type
        uuid entity_id
        jsonb old_values
        jsonb new_values
        string ip_address
        timestamp created_at
    }

    SYSTEM_SETTINGS {
        uuid id PK
        string key UK
        string value
        text description
        timestamp updated_at
    }
```

### Relationship Summary

| Relationship | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| User → Branch | Many-to-One | Staff/managers belong to a branch; admins & customers are branch-agnostic |
| Branch → Slot | One-to-Many | Each branch publishes its own slots |
| ServiceType → Slot | One-to-Many | Each slot is for one service type |
| User ↔ ServiceType | Many-to-Many | Via `staff_service_type` junction |
| Slot → Appointment | One-to-Many | A slot can host `max_bookings` appointments |
| User → Appointment | One-to-Many | Customers book; staff are optionally assigned |
| User → AuditLog | One-to-Many | Every sensitive action is logged |

